The paper deals with the problem of recommendation systems, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus is on implicit feedback, which is a common problem in recommendation systems, and the proposed algorithm uses tensor factorization, which is a technique commonly used in data science and machine learning (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the incorporation of contextual information into the model, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper presents experimental results on several datasets, which suggests that the authors may have used techniques from data science and statistics (cs.DS) to analyze the results.
